therichastill
Stevenage, UK3,423 contributions
Let's Go Round Again
Sep 2024 • Solo
The Placa d'Espanya is on the centre of a very large grand roundabout. There are a number of busy roads stretching off from it in different directions.

There are some very impressive buildings on all sides of it along with a grand structure in the middle. Unfortunately when I visited it was under restoration so it was difficult to see it.

At the moment I would recommend going to the Centro Commercial Arenas de Barcelona and going up to the top of the building so you can look down on it from above. In my opinion it's the best way to take it all in.

Keep your eyes open when trying to cross the roads. Cars and buses come tearing past in different directions so wait for the right time to cross and don't risk a quick dash across the road!
Written October 28, 2024

Large plaza with grand structures surrounding!
May 2024 • Couples
The Placa d'Espanya is a grand square with a large traffic circle surrounded by artistic structures built for the 1929 exhibition. It has an impressive large fountain in the middle, but no water running now for three years due to the prolonged drought. The area is difficult to fully enjoy because of the heavy traffic and few areas for pedestrians.

So much history to see in this busy area.
Apr 2024 • Couples
Visited here on the way to the museum. It is a very high traffic area, but boasts so much to see it is worth putting up with the high levels of traffic. A number of iconic buildings and the spectacular view as you walk towards the museum. Unfortunately none of the fountains were operational due to the ongoing drought, but still spectacular to see. Easy access from public transportation.
